article.linkText: Williamson's 28 lead Seattle U past Idaho 92-55
article.story: SEATTLE -- — Kobe Williamson had 28 points in Seattle U's 92-55 victory over Idaho on Wednesday night. Williamson added six rebounds for the Redhawks (3-2). Brandton Chatfield scored 18 points and added eight rebounds. Paris Dawson had 11 points and was 3 of 5 shooting, including 2 for 3 from 3-point range, and went 3 for 4 from the line. Kyson Rose led the way for the Vandals (2-3) with 12 points and two steals. Quinn Denker added 10 points for Idaho. NEXT UP Both teams play UCSD next, Seattle U on Sunday at home and Idaho on Friday. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
